WEBVTT

00:02:10.880 --> 00:02:12.399
Major Ferguson reporting.

00:02:14.240 --> 00:02:14.960
Have a seat.

00:02:17.759 --> 00:02:18.840
Sorry, Major.

00:02:19.119 --> 00:02:20.000
You might have to

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:20.960
stay here a few more days.

00:02:21.359 --> 00:02:22.240
Why?

00:02:22.520 --> 00:02:24.399
After the British retreat,

00:02:24.479 --> 00:02:26.039
the Japs have blocked

00:02:26.039 --> 00:02:27.600
all our routes to the China theater.

00:02:27.920 --> 00:02:29.799
We're planning to open a new route.

00:02:30.439 --> 00:02:32.000
But I told them you're stuck here.

00:02:33.079 --> 00:02:33.399
Colonel,

00:02:33.399 --> 00:02:34.560
I must reach China

00:02:34.560 --> 00:02:35.200
by April fifteenth.

00:02:35.560 --> 00:02:36.560
We still have some time,

00:02:36.560 --> 00:02:37.879
but we must act fast.

00:02:38.719 --> 00:02:40.079
Look at this map.

00:02:41.000 --> 00:02:42.159
The only possible route

00:02:42.159 --> 00:02:43.799
is to fly over the Himalayas.

00:02:44.359 --> 00:02:46.680
Those peaks are five miles high.

00:02:47.159 --> 00:02:49.159
Our planes can't fly that high.

00:02:49.359 --> 00:02:51.200
We have no maps of that area yet.

00:02:51.200 --> 00:02:52.599
Radio navigation

00:02:52.959 --> 00:02:55.560
and the actual weather there are unknowns.

00:02:55.680 --> 00:02:56.000
Colonel,

00:02:56.000 --> 00:02:56.599
it sounds like you're saying our mission

00:02:56.599 --> 00:02:57.640
is impossible.

00:02:59.000 --> 00:03:00.319
Don't give up yet, Major.

00:03:00.519 --> 00:03:01.920
Our pilots are pioneering

00:03:01.920 --> 00:03:03.439
a route over the Himalayas.

00:03:03.680 --> 00:03:05.640
You'll have to stand by until departure.

00:03:15.439 --> 00:03:17.040
Seven-Seven-Zero-Three,

00:03:17.120 --> 00:03:20.400
prepare for takeoff on a two-hundred-fifty-meter runway.

00:03:20.959 --> 00:03:23.840
Seven-Seven-Zero-Three, ready.

00:03:25.200 --> 00:03:27.519
Seven-Seven-Zero-Three, cleared for takeoff.

00:03:37.359 --> 00:03:39.199
Well done, Jimmy.

00:03:39.319 --> 00:03:40.400
I'm very pleased

00:03:40.400 --> 00:03:41.240
with your pilots' performance.

00:03:41.520 --> 00:03:41.879
Colonel,

00:03:41.879 --> 00:03:43.240
since you proposed this crazy idea,

00:03:43.240 --> 00:03:44.919
we've certainly accomplished a lot.

00:03:46.080 --> 00:03:47.159
The boys were initially convinced

00:03:47.159 --> 00:03:48.800
they were going to bomb Hitler.

00:03:48.800 --> 00:03:49.240
That's fine.

00:03:49.240 --> 00:03:50.840
We are considering bombing Hitler.

00:03:52.280 --> 00:03:52.680
Jimmy,

00:03:53.159 --> 00:03:54.560
Admiral Halsey will soon arrive in

00:03:54.560 --> 00:03:55.800
San Francisco.

00:03:55.960 --> 00:03:56.400
He wants

00:03:56.400 --> 00:03:58.000
you to brief him on this mission.

00:03:58.599 --> 00:04:01.240
Even though I saw your good work today,

00:04:01.240 --> 00:04:03.240
the Navy still isn't confident a bomber

00:04:03.240 --> 00:04:04.599
fully loaded with fuel and bombs

00:04:04.599 --> 00:04:08.400
can take off from a carrier.

00:04:08.520 --> 00:04:10.560
I'd be happy to test-fly from a carrier myself,

00:04:10.560 --> 00:04:12.280
to show the Admiral.

00:04:12.280 --> 00:04:13.439
Good, you do it.

00:04:13.759 --> 00:04:16.280
That would be the most convincing proof.

00:04:17.520 --> 00:04:18.319
I've heard

00:04:19.039 --> 00:04:20.439
your squadron's B-25s

00:04:20.439 --> 00:04:21.520
can't all fit on

00:04:21.520 --> 00:04:22.719
the Hornet's deck.

00:04:24.280 --> 00:04:26.199
That deck can only handle fifteen planes.

00:04:26.199 --> 00:04:28.400
Sixteen at best.

00:04:31.039 --> 00:04:32.439
That's a shame.

00:04:33.560 --> 00:04:34.800
With only sixteen, we can't

00:04:34.800 --> 00:04:36.159
do much damage to Tokyo.

00:04:37.360 --> 00:04:38.520
Even with all twenty-four,

00:04:38.520 --> 00:04:40.039
we wouldn't do much damage.

00:04:40.319 --> 00:04:40.719
Listen.

00:04:41.039 --> 00:04:42.000
The key to this mission is

00:04:42.000 --> 00:04:43.360
to warn the Japs,

00:04:43.360 --> 00:04:45.280
not to cause massive destruction.

00:04:46.080 --> 00:04:47.560
Not everyone gets to be a hero.

00:04:48.479 --> 00:04:50.919
Good pilots are needed for other missions.

00:04:51.800 --> 00:04:53.199
Those who don't go on this mission

00:04:53.840 --> 00:04:56.599
will be assigned to other duties.

00:04:56.919 --> 00:04:58.439
Maybe even bombing Hitler in Europe.

00:05:01.120 --> 00:05:02.879
Find a chance to tell the men, okay?

00:05:20.439 --> 00:05:21.360
Men,

00:05:24.599 --> 00:05:24.879
as of today,

00:05:24.879 --> 00:05:26.199
our first phase of training

00:05:26.199 --> 00:05:27.360
is nearly complete.

00:05:27.960 --> 00:05:29.280
I appreciate all the effort

00:05:29.280 --> 00:05:30.759
you've put into the B-25s.

00:05:31.280 --> 00:05:33.159
There's still a lot of work ahead.

00:05:33.319 --> 00:05:34.120
Colonel, do you mean

00:05:34.120 --> 00:05:35.879
adding another broomstick?

00:05:36.240 --> 00:05:36.680
I bet

00:05:36.680 --> 00:05:38.520
Hitler's scared shitless right now.

00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:42.080
Many keep asking me

00:05:42.080 --> 00:05:43.199
what this mission really is.

00:05:43.800 --> 00:05:46.040
I can only repeat what I've said before.

00:05:46.680 --> 00:05:48.040
This mission is extremely dangerous.

00:05:48.040 --> 00:05:49.519
This mission is extremely dangerous.

00:05:49.600 --> 00:05:50.759
Do not reveal to anyone

00:05:50.920 --> 00:05:52.759
what we're doing or where we're going.

00:05:53.160 --> 00:05:54.879
Not even if your mother asks.

00:05:55.519 --> 00:05:56.560
I'm talking to you.

00:05:57.879 --> 00:06:00.639
This is all top secret.

00:06:01.439 --> 00:06:02.439
I'll tell you later

00:06:02.439 --> 00:06:04.199
what you need to know.

00:06:05.199 --> 00:06:06.480
Any questions?

00:06:06.600 --> 00:06:07.959
No, sir.

00:06:07.959 --> 00:06:09.560
Anyone having second thoughts,

00:06:09.680 --> 00:06:11.160
anyone who wants out,

00:06:11.399 --> 00:06:13.319
tell me now and you can withdraw.

00:06:15.680 --> 00:06:16.319
Good.

00:06:17.480 --> 00:06:20.120
Tomorrow, our squadron's B-25s

00:06:20.759 --> 00:06:22.639
will all fly to

00:06:22.639 --> 00:06:23.839
McClellan Airfield in Sacramento.

00:06:24.639 --> 00:06:26.480
After the transfer,

00:06:26.600 --> 00:06:27.959
our training focus

00:06:27.959 --> 00:06:30.399
will be ultra-short takeoffs.

00:06:32.040 --> 00:06:34.240
A new crew of mechanics will be there.

00:06:34.519 --> 00:06:35.639
Lawson, Cole,

00:06:35.839 --> 00:06:38.079
I'm putting you two in charge of overseeing them.

00:06:38.160 --> 00:06:39.560
Speed things up.

00:06:39.560 --> 00:06:40.439
Yes, sir.

00:06:40.439 --> 00:06:41.399
That's all.

00:06:42.040 --> 00:06:42.720
Have a good evening.

00:06:43.240 --> 00:06:43.600
Alright.

00:06:44.600 --> 00:06:45.879
Ultra-short takeoffs.

00:06:48.439 --> 00:06:49.360
What'll you have today?

00:06:49.720 --> 00:06:50.639
Whiskey.

00:06:53.000 --> 00:06:53.160
Sir,

00:06:53.160 --> 00:06:55.000
are you really going to Europe to bomb Hitler?

00:06:56.199 --> 00:06:57.759
Hitler, Yamamoto, Mussolini...

00:06:57.800 --> 00:06:58.319
Take your pick.

00:06:58.360 --> 00:06:59.680
I'll fly you there myself to meet him.

00:06:59.680 --> 00:07:01.759
You can jump out and say hello.

00:07:05.120 --> 00:07:06.560
This one's on me.

00:07:16.199 --> 00:07:17.720
Dinner is now served.

00:07:17.720 --> 00:07:20.480
Guests may proceed to the dining room.

00:07:22.519 --> 00:07:23.360
Miss Ye.

00:07:23.399 --> 00:07:24.759
It's time for dinner.

00:07:31.839 --> 00:07:32.519
Care to join me?

00:07:33.079 --> 00:07:33.800
What?

00:07:35.360 --> 00:07:35.720
Well,

00:07:35.720 --> 00:07:37.519
the announcement just now said

00:07:37.519 --> 00:07:39.120
dinner is being served on board.

00:07:39.240 --> 00:07:39.879
Shall we go together?

00:07:41.040 --> 00:07:43.560
After all, we're the only two Chinese on the ship.

00:07:45.240 --> 00:07:45.920
Alright then.

00:07:46.720 --> 00:07:47.600
Wait for me a moment.

00:08:23.920 --> 00:08:26.319
Hello.

00:08:45.199 --> 00:08:46.240
What are you talking about?

00:08:50.199 --> 00:08:51.240
This Fukuda,

00:08:51.680 --> 00:08:53.519
he runs a trading company on the island.

00:08:54.240 --> 00:08:56.360
From Tanjiawan to Shangbiao Village

00:08:56.360 --> 00:08:58.040
To the air base naval dock

00:08:58.040 --> 00:08:59.040
He has shops everywhere.

00:08:59.839 --> 00:09:01.959
Even the cigarettes Commander Fujita smokes

00:09:02.040 --> 00:09:03.199
are supplied by him.

00:09:04.920 --> 00:09:06.079
He named all his shops

00:09:06.079 --> 00:09:07.800
"New Nagasaki."

00:09:08.519 --> 00:09:11.000
I think he wants to one day

00:09:11.000 --> 00:09:12.519
turn Sanzao Island into a new Nagasaki.

00:09:12.519 --> 00:09:14.439
That way, he'd be the supreme commander,

00:09:14.439 --> 00:09:16.879
and General Fujita would just be one of his generals.

00:09:18.759 --> 00:09:20.680
I just got a new batch of cigars

00:09:20.680 --> 00:09:21.800
from the concession in Shanghai.

00:09:21.800 --> 00:09:23.639
Let's go try them.

00:09:24.000 --> 00:09:24.600
Let's go.

00:09:31.360 --> 00:09:32.240
Let me tell you,

00:09:32.480 --> 00:09:33.399
that guy...

00:09:33.839 --> 00:09:35.360
He's the only one authorized by the island's

00:09:35.360 --> 00:09:36.879
Special Police Corps

00:09:37.000 --> 00:09:39.040
to run comfort stations.

00:09:40.279 --> 00:09:42.519
He hired over twenty immigrants from Okinawa

00:09:42.519 --> 00:09:43.600
to work for him.

00:09:44.399 --> 00:09:48.800
He deals in everything from daily goods to grain.

00:09:49.279 --> 00:09:50.199
Basically, anything

00:09:50.199 --> 00:09:52.600
that can be bought with money

00:09:54.000 --> 00:09:55.319
has some connection to him.

00:09:56.639 --> 00:09:57.560
Miss Ye,

00:09:57.680 --> 00:10:00.160
if you ever need anything on the island,

00:10:00.519 --> 00:10:01.399
you can come to me.

00:10:01.399 --> 00:10:03.360
After all, it's easier for me.

00:10:05.159 --> 00:10:06.039
Thank you.

00:10:06.039 --> 00:10:06.919
His

00:10:07.759 --> 00:10:09.919
darn backer is the Special Police Corps.

00:10:10.320 --> 00:10:11.759
But he's just

00:10:12.799 --> 00:10:14.639
one of Oshima Hiroshi's dogs.

00:10:18.799 --> 00:10:21.240
What brings you to the island this time?

00:10:22.519 --> 00:10:23.559
I'm going home.

00:10:24.360 --> 00:10:25.200
Home?

00:10:25.840 --> 00:10:27.279
My home is on Sanzao Island.

00:10:29.159 --> 00:10:30.840
My father is Ye Degong.

00:10:33.440 --> 00:10:35.519
So you're Ye Degong's daughter!

00:10:35.759 --> 00:10:36.840
You know my father?

00:10:36.840 --> 00:10:37.480
Of course.

00:10:38.399 --> 00:10:39.360
How is he?

00:10:39.960 --> 00:10:40.840
He's fine.

00:10:40.919 --> 00:10:41.559
He's doing well.

00:10:41.559 --> 00:10:42.720
His health is also very good.

00:10:43.399 --> 00:10:44.039
That's good to hear.

00:10:44.240 --> 00:10:45.799
I've long heard that Ye Degong's daughter

00:10:45.799 --> 00:10:46.840
was studying abroad.

00:10:46.840 --> 00:10:47.960
So it's you.

00:10:48.559 --> 00:10:49.480
Commander Fujita,

00:10:49.480 --> 00:10:51.080
when he was in the US before,

00:10:51.080 --> 00:10:52.360
served as a military attachÃ© assistant.

00:10:52.639 --> 00:10:54.840
Your father was a diplomat.

00:10:54.840 --> 00:10:56.039
So Commander Fujita

00:10:56.039 --> 00:10:57.879
very much enjoys chatting with your father.

00:10:59.399 --> 00:11:01.919
But perhaps because the military

00:11:01.919 --> 00:11:04.320
seized your family's mansion,

00:11:04.320 --> 00:11:05.279
your father

00:11:05.279 --> 00:11:06.759
hasn't been very welcoming.

00:11:59.279 --> 00:11:59.720
Hey!

00:12:00.279 --> 00:12:01.080
What's your business?

00:12:01.480 --> 00:12:03.600
From the Maintenance Association.

00:12:04.639 --> 00:12:06.519
Who sent you?

00:12:07.080 --> 00:12:09.440
Captain Inoue told me to come.

00:12:10.200 --> 00:12:11.000
Go on up.

00:12:11.679 --> 00:12:12.200
Okay.

00:12:31.879 --> 00:12:33.080
Chairman Tang.

00:12:35.399 --> 00:12:36.200
Upstairs,

00:12:39.639 --> 00:12:40.720
Captain Inoue...

00:12:41.559 --> 00:12:42.480
Chairman Tang.

00:12:43.120 --> 00:12:44.600
Can you guarantee

00:12:44.600 --> 00:12:46.320
your loyalty to the Imperial Army?

00:12:47.399 --> 00:12:48.320
Captain Inoue,

00:12:48.840 --> 00:12:50.120
my loyalty to the Imperial Army

00:12:50.120 --> 00:12:51.399
has always been unwavering.

00:12:51.440 --> 00:12:52.200
Wrong.

00:12:53.799 --> 00:12:56.000
You're hiding many things.

00:12:56.399 --> 00:12:56.960
No, no...

00:12:57.159 --> 00:12:57.720
No.

00:12:58.159 --> 00:12:59.720
Absolutely not!

00:13:09.039 --> 00:13:09.879
Recently,

00:13:10.200 --> 00:13:11.559
we've received some reports.

00:13:12.519 --> 00:13:14.120
In Shangbiao Village,

00:13:14.120 --> 00:13:15.799
Tanjiawan Village,

00:13:15.799 --> 00:13:17.679
and many other homes,

00:13:17.679 --> 00:13:19.240
there are secret rooms built.

00:13:20.919 --> 00:13:22.360
Why haven't you reported

00:13:23.279 --> 00:13:26.679
this matter to us?

00:13:28.200 --> 00:13:29.159
Captain Inoue,

00:13:29.519 --> 00:13:31.279
it... it's like this.

00:13:31.960 --> 00:13:33.919
Not every family on this island

00:13:33.919 --> 00:13:35.240
has a secret room.

00:13:35.720 --> 00:13:37.559
Poor families don't have secret rooms.

00:13:39.639 --> 00:13:40.480
Come up.

00:13:44.279 --> 00:13:45.120
Alright.

00:13:55.960 --> 00:13:56.840
Captain Inoue,

00:13:58.279 --> 00:13:59.440
you don't know,

00:14:00.639 --> 00:14:02.799
this area used to have pirate troubles.

00:14:03.639 --> 00:14:05.279
The wealthy families on the island,

00:14:06.080 --> 00:14:07.480
when building their mansions,

00:14:07.480 --> 00:14:08.840
they built secret rooms.

00:14:08.840 --> 00:14:10.279
When pirates came,

00:14:10.679 --> 00:14:12.279
to hide valuables,

00:14:12.279 --> 00:14:14.279
family members, and food.

00:14:14.720 --> 00:14:15.399
I see.

00:14:16.159 --> 00:14:17.080
So then,

00:14:17.399 --> 00:14:19.200
does the Tan family in the east of the village have one?

00:14:19.679 --> 00:14:20.159
Yes.

00:14:20.759 --> 00:14:22.559
What about that Old Chen

00:14:22.559 --> 00:14:23.519
from the ancestral hall last time?

00:14:23.519 --> 00:14:24.159
Yes.

00:14:24.559 --> 00:14:26.000
Ye Degong, does the Ye family have one too?

00:14:26.000 --> 00:14:26.759
Yes, they do.

00:14:35.559 --> 00:14:36.799
So tell me,

00:14:37.440 --> 00:14:40.360
where do these wealthy families

00:14:40.559 --> 00:14:42.039
usually build their secret rooms?

00:14:42.360 --> 00:14:42.799
This...

00:14:42.799 --> 00:14:44.320
I really don't know.

00:14:45.080 --> 00:14:48.159
I've heard some are built in attics,

00:14:48.159 --> 00:14:50.039
and some are built underground.

00:14:50.399 --> 00:14:51.840
Secret rooms are secret rooms.

00:14:52.039 --> 00:14:54.720
They must be in secret places.

00:14:55.360 --> 00:14:56.360
That makes sense.

00:14:56.919 --> 00:14:58.759
So, does anyone on the island know?

00:14:59.600 --> 00:15:00.799
No.

00:15:00.799 --> 00:15:01.159
These...

00:15:01.759 --> 00:15:02.919
These wealthy families,

00:15:03.440 --> 00:15:04.600
when they build secret rooms,

00:15:04.600 --> 00:15:06.600
hire people from off the island.

00:15:07.000 --> 00:15:08.720
People on the island can't find them.

00:15:09.600 --> 00:15:11.759
Tang...

00:15:12.759 --> 00:15:13.840
You know

00:15:14.720 --> 00:15:16.919
the consequences of hiding things from me.

00:15:17.759 --> 00:15:18.559
No!

00:15:18.559 --> 00:15:20.279
I ab-absolutely wouldn't dare!

00:15:20.720 --> 00:15:23.120
Every word I said is true!

00:15:25.399 --> 00:15:26.000
Alright.

00:15:27.840 --> 00:15:28.879
Today,

00:15:29.120 --> 00:15:30.360
I called you here

00:15:30.919 --> 00:15:33.320
for a very important matter

00:15:33.639 --> 00:15:35.559
that your Maintenance Association must handle.

00:15:39.080 --> 00:15:40.279
A few days ago,

00:15:40.279 --> 00:15:42.799
we shot down an American plane.

00:15:43.639 --> 00:15:46.200
One person from the plane is still missing.

00:15:46.639 --> 00:15:48.600
Your Association will notify

00:15:48.600 --> 00:15:50.200
all the villagers on the island.

00:15:51.360 --> 00:15:53.159
Anyone providing a lead

00:15:53.799 --> 00:15:56.440
will be rewarded by our Special Police Corps

00:15:56.440 --> 00:15:58.679
with fifty jin of rice

00:15:59.320 --> 00:16:01.279
and twenty jin of pork.

00:16:02.200 --> 00:16:02.960
But,

00:16:03.480 --> 00:16:05.000
if anyone withholds information

00:16:05.000 --> 00:16:07.799
or intentionally hides someone,

00:16:10.080 --> 00:16:11.840
their entire family will be shot.

00:16:12.519 --> 00:16:13.440
Understood?

00:16:13.559 --> 00:16:14.200
Und-

00:16:15.039 --> 00:16:16.080
Understood.

00:16:16.960 --> 00:16:17.679
Good.

00:16:17.840 --> 00:16:18.639
Then

00:16:19.519 --> 00:16:20.360
you may go.

00:16:31.960 --> 00:16:33.639
It seems there really are secret rooms on the island.

00:16:33.639 --> 00:16:36.399
I really admire you.

00:16:36.399 --> 00:16:38.080
How did you know?

00:16:38.919 --> 00:16:41.440
Even an old woman who does laundry and cooking

00:16:41.440 --> 00:16:42.440
has a hidden cellar in her home.

00:16:42.440 --> 00:16:43.440
Other families wouldn't be without them.

00:16:43.840 --> 00:16:45.080
I see.

00:16:45.960 --> 00:16:48.799
This American who fell from the plane

00:16:48.799 --> 00:16:50.440
either drowned in the sea,

00:16:50.440 --> 00:16:52.159
his hat washed ashore,

00:16:53.000 --> 00:16:53.759
or,

00:16:53.759 --> 00:16:55.320
he's currently hiding

00:16:55.320 --> 00:16:57.639
in a secret room in some village house.

00:16:57.639 --> 00:16:59.080
That's why we found nothing in our search.

00:16:59.080 --> 00:17:01.039
So you think

00:17:02.600 --> 00:17:03.720
Ye Degong

00:17:04.240 --> 00:17:06.639
